title: Eulonchiella
data: Eulonchiella is an extinct genus of small-headed flies in the family Acroceridae. It is known from Baltic amber from the Eocene, though the locality is unknown (possibly Russia). It contains only one species, Eulonchiella eocenica.[1] This article related to members of the fly superfamily Nemestrinoidea is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.
